"cell_type": "markdown",
"id": "explanation-generate-key",
"metadata": {},
"source": [
"## 2. Generating a Vulnerable Key Instance\n",
"\n",
"This function performs the RSA key generation, intentionally making the key pair weak by choosing a small private exponent $\mathbf{d}$.\n",
"\n",
"1.  Vulnerability Threshold: It calculates the maximum safe size for $\mathbf{d}$ based on the $n^{1/4}$ limit.\n",
"2.  Small $\mathbf{d}$: It chooses a small $\mathbf{d}$ to ensure $\mathbf{d \ll n^{1/4}}$ to guarantee the success of the attack for demonstration purposes.\n",
"3.  Public Key $\mathbf{e}$: Calculated as the modular inverse: $\mathbf{e} \equiv \mathbf{d}^{\mathbf{-1}} \pmod{\phi(\mathbf{n})}$."
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
