"## 3. The Wiener Attack Logic\n",
"\n",
"This function implements the core attack by iterating through the convergent fractions $\mathbf{k/d_{\text{cand}}}$ of the public ratio $\mathbf{e/n}$.\n",
"\n",
"### Verification Steps:\n",
"\n",
"1.  Test $\mathbf{\phi}$ Integrity: Check if the calculated $\phi_{\text{cand}}$ is an integer: $\mathbf{(ed_{\text{cand}} - 1) \equiv 0 \pmod{k}}$.\n",
"2.  Test Factorization: If $\phi_{\text{cand}}$ is an integer, use it to solve the quadratic equation $\mathbf{x^2 - (n - \phi_{\text{cand}} + 1)x + n = 0}$. The attack succeeds only if the discriminant of this quadratic is a perfect square, yielding integer factors $p$ and $q$."
]
},
